physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Lungs were clear. An electrocardiogram (ECG) showed sinus rhythm at 130 beats per minute and possible left atrial enlargement.
Marked anxiety and increased dyspnea; approximately 200 ml of frothy, pink secretions were suctioned during manual ventilation.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Blood pressure rose to 201/176 mm Hg and pulse to 173 bpm before transient fall to 76/43 mm Hg.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Diaphoretic skin; crackles at both lung bases; heart sounds rapid and regular. Abdomen soft and non-distended.
Left ventricular ejection fraction improved to 46%; left ventricular size and left atrial size had decreased.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Ejection fraction changed as follows: 27% on day 1, 36% on day 6, 39% at 2 months, 46% at 7 months follow-up.
